      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APPIN WAY (2) has been hard to follow lately, running fifth (23.38) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. Will find this more suitable and can atone. DANDY REDEEMER (3) finds it hard to win. Finished in the money last time though when third (18.90) at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Leading player again. SHE'S OUR JOY (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (30.51) last time in a Mix 2/3 at Wentworth Park. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Better than last start and can bounce back. BY THE BOOK (4) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
